Class I18nReportableEnum

@Persistent
public abstract class I18nReportableEnum
extends AbstractReportable
implements Comparable<I18nReportableEnum>

An enum-like suport class that supports injection of descriptions (from resource bundles).

To ease implementation of format validation, this class does not limit the value set. Instances could be created for unknown values, they are then marked as invalid.

Subclasses shall invoke the initValues(java.lang.Class, java.util.Properties, int[]) method upon descriptions injection to get a {#link Map} of valid values. Any value not present in the map should be considered invalid.

initValues

protected static <T extends I18nReportableEnum> Map<Integer,T> initValues(Class<T> clazz,
                                                                          Properties props,
                                                                          int[] values)
Initializes the list of known (i.e. valid) values. In case the resource bundle should not be trusted, the subclasses should provide the list of allowed values. Values not present in this array are ignored.

Parameters:
clazz - the concrete subclass.
props - the resource bundle to load descriptions from.
values - the list of valid values or null if the resource bundle can be trusted.
Returns:
a Map associating integer keys to subclass instances for valid values.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if clazz or props is null.
RuntimeException - to wrap any error raised by subclass constructor.
